latestPosts.caption:
Do you struggle to control yourself around bakery items and sweet? 

I definitely do. 
Here’s what I do to try and keep things in check while still enjoying my favourite sweet treats! 

- Limit not eliminate. 

- Generally eat more protein and fat in my diet (this keeps me fuller and I find I have less sugar cravings).

- Drink a glass or water and see if I still want it as much, more often than not I’m just thirsty. 

- Eat it as dessert after a full meal so I’m already quite full and probably won’t be able to eat it all. 

- Share it so I end up eating a part of it and not the whole thing.

#food #sugar #balance

latestPosts.caption:
I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again, build your back up!
I’ve spent much of my time this year focusing on strengthening my back with various exercises including god knows how many pull-ups, back extensions and rows. 
Surprisingly one move has stood out as the move I feel has helped me the most - the straight arm dumbbell pull back - deceptively easy looking but a game changer and by far my exercise of the year. 
Add it to your workouts and see the magic happen 🪄✨
